Chile applies a conservative approach for term deposits as the local DGS covers the amount by client not by entity, thus as they cannot be sure of the total amount of term deposits in the system of our clients. Therefore, Chile is not including any term deposit as covered.

Argentina and Uruguay are showing lower levels due to the USD deposits not covered by the DGS.

